					<row><cell><p>N:</p></cell><cell>Non-</cell></row>
					<row><cell/><cell>homogeneous</cell></row>
				</tabular>
			</p>
		</aside>

		<aside component="hard"><title>Abbreviations</title>
			<p>
				<tabular>
					<col width="5%"/>
					<col />
					<col width="5%"/>
					<col />
					<row>
						<cell><p>DE:</p></cell><cell>Differential Equation</cell>
						<cell><p>IVP:</p></cell><cell>Initial-Value Problem</cell>
					</row>
					<row>
						<cell><p>L:</p></cell><cell>Linear</cell>
						<cell><p>H:</p></cell><cell>Homogeneous</cell>
					</row>
					<row>
						<cell><p>CC:</p></cell><cell>Constant Coefficient</cell>
						<cell><p>N:</p></cell><cell>Nonhomogeneous</cell>
					</row>
				</tabular>
			</p>
		</aside>

		<table>
			<title>Core Proficiency Topics</title>
			<tabular bottom="minor" top="minor" left="minor" right="minor">
				<col halign="left" valign="top" width="19%"/>
				<col halign="left" width="81%"/>
				<row>
					<cell><term>Topic</term></cell>
					<cell><term>To demonstrate proficiency, be able to:</term></cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C1</term>:</line><line>Solutions of DEs</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Define the general and particular solutions of a DE or IVP.</line>
							<line>Determine whether a given function is a solution to a DE or IVP, and explain how your work supports the conclusion.</line>
							<line>Use initial condition(s) to find a particular solution.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C2</term>:</line><line>Separable DEs</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Determine whether a DE is separable and write it in separable form.</line>
							<line>Solve separable equations correctly, including the proper use of logarithms and absolute values and correct handling of constants, with the solution in simplest form.</line>
							<line>Apply initial condition(s) when provided.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C3</term>:</line><line>Integrating Factor</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Recognize when the integrating factor method applies.</line>
							<line>Find the integrating factor and use it to simplify a DE.</line>
							<line>Solve linear first-order equations using an integrating factor, including correct use of logarithms/absolute values and constants, with the solution in simplest form.</line>
							<line>Apply initial condition(s) when provided.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C4</term>:</line><line>LHCC Equations</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Recognize when the LHCC technique applies.</line>
							<line>Form the characteristic equation and use it appropriately.</line>
							<line>Solve linear, homogeneous equations with constant coefficients using the characteristic equation.</line>
							<line>Apply initial condition(s) when provided.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C5</term>:</line><line>LNCC Equations</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Determine when the method of undetermined coefficients applies.</line>
							<line>Identify an appropriate form for the particular solution <m>y_p</m>.</line>
							<line>Solve linear, nonhomogeneous equations with constant coefficients using undetermined coefficients.</line>
							<line>Apply initial condition(s) when provided.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C6</term>:</line><line>Laplace Transforms</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Decide when solving with Laplace transforms is appropriate.</line>
							<line>Solve differential equations using Laplace transforms.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>C7</term>:</line><line>Approximating Solutions</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Describe the difference between an Analytic vs Numerical Solution.</line>
							<line>Approximate the solution to a first-order DE using Euler's Method.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>
			</tabular>
		</table>
	</subsection>

	<subsection xml:id="ma311-secondary-topics">
		<title>Secondary Topics</title>

		<p>
			In addition to the core topics, there are 13 secondary topics. These cover supporting skills and applications. You only need to pass each secondary topic once, and they are only assessed on in-class ODPs. While you must pass all core topics to earn a C or higher, proficiency in secondary topics can help raise your grade to a B or an A.
		</p>

		<table>
			<title>Secondary Proficiency Topics (Tentative)</title>
			<tabular bottom="minor" top="minor" left="minor" right="minor">
				<col halign="left" width="25%"/>
				<col halign="left" width="75%"/>
				<row>
					<cell><term>Topic</term></cell>
					<cell><term>To demonstrate proficiency, be able to:</term></cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S1</term>:</line><line>Classify DEs 1</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Identify the order of a DE.</line>
							<line>Determine whether a DE is linear or nonlinear.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S2</term>:</line><line>Classify DEs 2</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Determine whether a DE is homogeneous or nonhomogeneous.</line>
							<line>Decide whether a DE has constant coefficients.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S3</term>:</line><line>LNCC 1</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Make a correct first guess for the particular solution <m>y_p</m>.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S4</term>:</line><line>LNCC 2</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Decide when the first guess for <m>y_p</m> must be adjusted.</line>
							<line>Make and justify the correct adjustment to the guess for <m>y_p</m> when needed.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S5</term>:</line><line>Forward Transform</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Use a provided table to compute a forward Laplace transform.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S6</term>:</line><line>Inverse Transform</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>Use a provided table to compute an inverse Laplace transform.</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S7</term>:</line><line>Step Functions 1</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Rewrite a piecewise function in unit step form.</line>
							<line>Sketch a function involving step functions.</line>
							<line>Write a discontinuous function using step functions.</line>
							<line>Evaluate unit step functions correctly.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S8</term>:</line><line>Step Functions 2</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Transform a piecewise function using unit step functions.</line>
							<line>Find an inverse transform of a function involving step functions.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S9</term>:</line><line>Discontinuous Forcing</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Solve a LNCC equation with a discontinuous forcing term.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S10</term>:</line><line>Slope Fields &amp; Equilibria</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Create a slope field for a DE.</line>
							<line>Sketch solution curves for an IVP on a slope field.</line>
							<line>Determine the stability of equilibria for autonomous DEs.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S11</term>:</line><line>Numerical Solution</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>Find the numerical solution for an IVP and interpret the result.</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S12</term>:</line><line>Systems of DEs</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Model scenarios using systems of DEs.</line>
							<line>Find a numerical solution for a system of DEs.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>

				<row>
					<cell><p><line><term>S13</term>:</line><line>Higher-Order DEs</line></p></cell>
					<cell>
						<p>
							<line>Convert a high-order DE into a system of 1st-order DEs.</line>
							<line>Find a numerical solution for a higher-order DE (directly or via system conversion) and interpret the result.</line>
						</p>
					</cell>
				</row>
			</tabular>
		</table>

		<p>
			<em>Note: This secondary topics list is tentative and subject to change.</em>
		</p>
	</subsection>

</section>